Effects of a group-based exercise program on the physical performance, muscle 
strength and quality of life in older women.

Eyigor S(1), Karapolat H, Durmaz B.

Author information:
(1)Ege University, Faculty of Medicine, Physical Therapy and Rehabilitation 
Department, 35100 Bornova-Izmir, Turkey. eyigor@hotmail.com

This study was aimed at determining the effect of a group-based exercise program 
on the physical performance, muscle strength and quality of life (QoL) in older 
women. Twenty women performed an exercise program for 8 weeks, at the 
rehabilitation unit. Outcome measures included a 4-m and 20-m walk test, a 6-min 
walk test, stair climbing and chair rise time, timed up and go test, isokinetic 
muscle testing of the knee and ankle, and the short form-36 (SF-36) and 
